 EMFULENI
Municipality reportedly owes South Africa’s power utility R2.3 billion. There is a judgement that was
issued to collect R615 million out of the R2.3 billion debt that Emfuleni
Municipality owes Eskom. Eskom Spokesperson Sikonathi
Mantshantsha said Eskom has issued another summons to collect the balance. “Sheriff of the Court removing
municipal property to enforce judgement for the non-payment of Eskom R635
million debt by the Emfuleni Local Municipality right now. “This is at the main municipality
building at Vanderbijlpark,” said Mantshantsha on his Twitter page.   